flavor: The user engages its gears to raise the Attack and Sp. Atk stats of ally Pokémon with the Plus or Minus Ability.

name: Throat Chop
flavor: The user attacks the target’s throat, and the resultant suffering prevents the target from using moves that emit sound for two turns.

name: Pollen Puff
flavor: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a pollen puff that restores its HP instead.

name: Anchor Shot
flavor: The user entangles the target with its anchor chain while attacking. The target becomes unable to flee.

name: Psychic Terrain
flavor: This protects Pokémon on the ground from priority moves and powers up Psychic-type moves for five turns.

name: Lunge
flavor: The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with full force. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Fire Lash
flavor: The user strikes the target with a burning lash. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Power Trip
flavor: The user boasts its strength and attacks the target. The more the user’s stats are raised, the greater the move’s power.

name: Burn Up
flavor: To inflict massive damage, the user burns itself out. After using this move, the user will no longer be Fire type.

name: Speed Swap
flavor: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.

name: Smart Strike
flavor: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

name: Purify
flavor: The user heals the target’s status condition. If the move succeeds, it also restores the user’s own HP.

name: Revelation Dance
flavor: The user attacks the target by dancing very hard. The user’s type determines the type of this move.

name: Core Enforcer
flavor: If the Pokémon the user has inflicted damage on have already used their moves, this move eliminates the effect of the target’s Ability.

name: Trop Kick
flavor: The user lands an intense kick of tropical origins on the target. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

name: Instruct
flavor: The user instructs the target to use the target’s last move again.

name: Beak Blast
flavor: The user first heats up its beak, and then it attacks the target. Making direct contact with the Pokémon while it’s heating up its beak results in a burn.

name: Clanging Scales
flavor: The user rubs the scales on its entire body and makes a huge noise to attack the opposing Pokémon. The user’s Defense stat goes down after the attack.|The user rubs the scales on its entire body and makes a huge noise to attack opposing Pokémon. The user’s Defense stat goes down after the attack.

name: Dragon Hammer
flavor: The user uses its body like a hammer to attack the target and inflict damage.

name: Brutal Swing
flavor: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

name: Aurora Veil
flavor: This move reduces damage from physical and special moves for five turns. This can be used only in a hailstorm.

name: Shell Trap
flavor: The user sets a shell trap. If the user is hit by a physical move, the trap will explode and inflict damage on the opposing Pokémon.|The user sets a shell trap. If the user is hit by a physical move, the trap will explode and inflict damage on opposing Pokémon.

name: Fleur Cannon
flavor: The user unleashes a strong beam. The attack’s recoil harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Psychic Fangs
flavor: The user bites the target with its psychic capabilities. This can also destroy Light Screen and Reflect.

name: Stomping Tantrum
flavor: Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. If the user’s previous move has failed, the power of this move doubles.

name: Shadow Bone
flavor: The user attacks by beating the target with a bone that contains a spirit. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Accelerock
flavor: The user smashes into the target at high speed. This move always goes first.

name: Liquidation
flavor: The user slams into the target using a full-force blast of water. This may also lower the target’s Defense stat.

name: Prismatic Laser
flavor: The user shoots powerful lasers using the power of a prism. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Spectral Thief
flavor: The user hides in the target’s shadow, steals the target’s stat boosts, and then attacks.

name: Sunsteel Strike
flavor: The user slams into the target with the force of a meteor. This move can be used on the target  regardless of its Abilities.|The user slams into the target with the force of a meteor. This move can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities.

name: Moongeist Beam
flavor: The user emits a sinister ray to attack the target. This move can be used on the target regardless of  its Abilities.|The user emits a sinister ray to attack the target. This move can be used on the target regardless of its Abilities.

name: Tearful Look
flavor: The user gets teary eyed to make the target lose its combative spirit. This lowers the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

name: Zing Zap
flavor: A strong electric blast crashes down on the target, giving it an electric shock. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Natures Madness
flavor: The user hits the target with the force of nature. It halves the target’s HP.

name: Multi Attack
flavor: Cloaking itself in high energy, the user slams into the target. The memory held determines the move’s type.

name: Mind Blown
flavor: The user attacks everything around it by causing its own head to explode. This also damages the user.

name: Plasma Fists
flavor: The user attacks with electrically charged fists. This move changes Normal-type moves to Electric-type moves.

name: Photon Geyser
flavor: The user attacks a target with a pillar of light. This move inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage—whichever stat is higher for the user.

name: Double Iron Bash
flavor: The user rotates, centering the hex nut in its chest, and then strikes with its arms twice in a row. This may also make the target flinch.

name: Max Guard
flavor: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

name: Dynamax Cannon
flavor: The user unleashes a strong beam from its core. This move deals twice the damage if the target is Dynamaxed.

name: Snipe Shot
flavor: The user ignores the effects of opposing Pokémon’s moves and Abilities that draw in moves, allowing this move to hit the chosen target.

name: Jaw Lock
flavor: This move prevents the user and the target from switching out until either of them faints. The effect goes away if either of the Pokémon leaves the field.

name: Stuff Cheeks
flavor: The user eats its held Berry, then sharply raises its Defense stat.

name: No Retreat
flavor: This move raises all the user’s stats but prevents the user from switching out or fleeing.

name: Tar Shot
flavor: The user pours sticky tar over the target, lowering the target’s Speed stat. The target becomes weaker to Fire-type moves.

name: Magic Powder
flavor: The user scatters a cloud of magic powder that changes the target to Psychic type.

name: Dragon Darts
flavor: The user attacks twice using Dreepy. If there are two targets, this move hits each target once.

name: Teatime
flavor: The user has teatime with all the Pokémon in the battle. Each Pokémon eats its held Berry.

name: Octolock
flavor: The user locks the target in and prevents it from fleeing. This move also lowers the target’s Defense and Sp. Def every turn.

name: Bolt Beak
flavor: The user stabs the target with its electrified beak. If the user attacks before the target, the power of this move is doubled.

name: Fishious Rend
flavor: The user rends the target with its hard gills. If the user attacks before the target, the power of this move is doubled.

name: Court Change
flavor: With its mysterious power, the user swaps the effects on either side of the field.

name: Clangorous Soul
flavor: The user raises all its stats by using some of its HP.

name: Body Press
flavor: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target. The higher the user’s Defense, the more damage it can inflict on the target.

name: Decorate
flavor: The user sharply raises the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats by decorating the target.

name: Drum Beating
flavor: The user plays its drum, controlling the drum’s roots to attack the target. This also lowers the target’s Speed stat.

name: Snap Trap
flavor: The user snares the target in a snap trap for four to five turns.

name: Pyro Ball
flavor: The user attacks by igniting a small stone and launching it as a fiery ball at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Behemoth Blade
flavor: The user becomes a gigantic sword and cuts the target. This move deals twice the damage if the target is Dynamaxed.

name: Behemoth Bash
flavor: The user becomes a gigantic shield and slams into the target. This move deals twice the damage if the target is Dynamaxed.

name: Aura Wheel
flavor: Morpeko attacks and raises its Speed with the energy stored in its cheeks. This move’s type changes depending on the user’s form.

name: Breaking Swipe
flavor: The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

name: Branch Poke
flavor: The user attacks the target by poking it with a sharply pointed branch.

name: Overdrive
flavor: The user attacks opposing Pokémon by twanging a guitar or bass guitar, causing a huge echo and strong vibration.

name: Apple Acid
flavor: The user attacks the target with an acidic liquid created from tart apples. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

name: Grav Apple
flavor: The user inflicts damage by dropping an apple from high above. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Spirit Break
flavor: The user attacks the target with so much force that it could break the target’s spirit. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Strange Steam
flavor: The user attacks the target by emitting steam. This may also confuse the target.

name: Life Dew
flavor: The user scatters mysterious water around and restores the HP of itself and its ally Pokémon in the battle.

name: Obstruct
flavor: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession. Direct contact harshly lowers the attacker’s Defense stat.

name: False Surrender
flavor: The user pretends to bow its head, but then it stabs the target with its disheveled hair. This attack never misses.

name: Meteor Assault
flavor: The user attacks wildly with its thick leek. The user can’t move on the next turn, because the force of this move makes it stagger.

name: Eternabeam
flavor: This is Eternatus’s most powerful attack in its original form. The user can’t move on the next turn.

name: Steel Beam
flavor: The user fires a beam of steel that it collected from its entire body. This also damages the user.

name: Expanding Force
flavor: The user attacks the target with its psychic power. This move’s power goes up and damages all opposing Pokémon on Psychic Terrain.

name: Steel Roller
flavor: The user attacks while destroying the terrain. This move fails when the ground hasn’t turned into a terrain.

name: Scale Shot
flavor: The user attacks by shooting scales two to five times in a row. This move boosts the user’s Speed stat but lowers its Defense stat.

name: Meteor Beam
flavor: In this two-turn attack, the user gathers space power and boosts its Sp. Atk stat, then attacks the target on the next turn.

name: Shell Side Arm
flavor: This move inflicts physical or special damage, whichever will be more effective. This may also poison the target.

name: Misty Explosion
flavor: The user attacks everything around it and faints upon using this move. This move’s power is increased on Misty Terrain.

name: Grassy Glide
flavor: Gliding on the ground, the user attacks the target. This move always goes first on Grassy Terrain.

name: Rising Voltage
flavor: The user attacks with electric voltage rising from the ground. This move’s power doubles when the target is on Electric Terrain.

name: Terrain Pulse
flavor: The user utilizes the power of the terrain to attack. This move’s type and power changes depending on the terrain when it’s used.

name: Skitter Smack
flavor: The user skitters behind the target to attack. This also lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

name: Burning Jealousy
flavor: The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted during the turn with a burn.

name: Lash Out
flavor: The user lashes out to vent its frustration toward the target. If the user’s stats were lowered during this turn, the power of this move is doubled.

name: Poltergeist
flavor: The user attacks the target by controlling the target’s item. The move fails if the target doesn’t have an item.

name: Corrosive Gas
flavor: The user surrounds everything around it with highly acidic gas and melts away items they hold.

name: Coaching
flavor: The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon, boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

name: Flip Turn
flavor: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

name: Triple Axel
flavor: A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more powerful with each successful hit.

name: Dual Wingbeat
flavor: The user slams the target with its wings. The target is hit twice in a row.

name: Scorching Sands
flavor: The user throws scorching sand at the target to attack. This may also leave the target with a burn.

name: Jungle Healing
flavor: The user becomes one with the jungle, restoring HP and healing any status conditions of itself and its ally Pokémon in battle.

name: Wicked Blow
flavor: The user, having mastered the Dark style, strikes the target with a fierce blow. This attack always results in a critical hit.

name: Surging Strikes
flavor: The user, having mastered the Water style, strikes the target with a flowing motion three times in a row. This attack always results in a critical hit.

name: Thunder Cage
flavor: The user traps the target in a cage of sparking electricity for four to five turns.

name: Dragon Energy
flavor: Converting its life-force into power, the user attacks opposing Pokémon. The lower the user’s HP, the lower the move’s power.

name: Freezing Glare
flavor: The user shoots its psychic power from its eyes to attack. This may also leave the target frozen.

name: Fiery Wrath
flavor: The user transforms its wrath into a fire-like aura to attack. This may also make opposing Pokémon flinch.

name: Thunderous Kick
flavor: The user overwhelms the target with lightning-like movement before delivering a kick. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

name: Glacial Lance
flavor: The user attacks by hurling a blizzard-cloaked icicle lance at opposing Pokémon.

name: Astral Barrage
flavor: The user attacks by sending a frightful amount of small ghosts at opposing Pokémon.

name: Eerie Spell
flavor: The user attacks with its tremendous psychic power. This also removes 3 PP from the target’s last move.

name: Psyshield Bash
flavor: Cloaking itself in psychic energy, the user slams into the target. This may also raise the user’s defensive stats.
